## Plan size limits
- See `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Plan size limits` for the canonical 4 MB hard cap and per-list caps (steps ≤ 500, scope_items ≤ 200, AC ≤ 500, evidence per step ≤ 500). A plan that exceeds any cap is rejected with `PlanArtifactSizeError` before Pydantic runs.

## Model tier
- See `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Model tier` for the `design.planning_profile` choice and bias-fill preset contract. Cheap models use `"minimal"` / `"balanced"`; high-quality models handcraft all seven design sub-sections plus `design.outcome` and `design.notes`.

## Cycle guard
- See `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Cycle guard` for the `depends_on` cycle validation contract (DAG only; diamond-shaped DAGs accepted).

Native file and shell tools are disabled in this brokered fallback; native orchestration tools remain enabled. Use the plan tools and {{SUBMIT_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} exactly as named below. Step mutation tools echo the new step number(s), the `depends_on` reindex map, and the AC ids whose `satisfied_by_steps` were rewritten.

Unless the plan is genuinely short, submit each required section separately.
- Use {{SUBMIT_PLAN_SECTION_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to stage `summary`, `skills_mcp`, `steps`, `critical_files`, `risks_mitigations`, and `verification_strategy`. If you rely on `design.planning_profile` or want the SE-opinionated design guidance, stage `design` before finalize.
- For small-to-medium plans, prefer {{SUBMIT_PLAN_SECTIONS_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to stage every section in one batched round-trip.
- Use {{VALIDATE_PLAN_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to dry-run the cross-section validator before finalize and {{GET_PLAN_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to inspect the staged draft if validation fails.
- Use {{FINALIZE_PLAN_TOOL_REFERENCE}} once all required sections are staged, and {{DISCARD_PLAN_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} only to throw the draft away.

For genuinely short plans, you may submit atomically via {{SUBMIT_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} with artifact_type="plan". `content` must be a JSON string of the RAW plan payload (not an outer artifact wrapper); do NOT send `{ "type": "plan", "content": ... }`.
